# ğŸŸ§ WebAssembly OpenGL Triangle Demo

This project compiles a simple C++ OpenGL ES 2.0 program (a single triangle) to **WebAssembly** using **Emscripten**, and runs it in the browser via a local development server.

---

### ğŸ“¦ Prerequisites

- Python 3.x
- Git
- **Emscripten SDK** (latest)

---

### ğŸš€ Setup Instructions (From Scratch)

### âœ… Step 1: Install Emscripten

#### ğŸ”§ Linux / macOS

```bash
git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git
cd emsdk
./emsdk install latest
./emsdk activate latest
source ./emsdk_env.sh
````

#### ğŸªŸ Windows (PowerShell)

```powershell
git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git
cd emsdk
.\emsdk install latest
.\emsdk activate latest
.\emsdk_env.ps1
```

> âœ… You must run `source ./emsdk_env.sh` or `.\emsdk_env.ps1` in **every new terminal session** to set up environment variables.

---

### âœ… Step 2: Clone the Project

```bash
git clone <your-project-repo>
cd <your-project-folder>
```

---

### âœ… Step 3: Build & Run

Use the provided `build_and_run.py` script:

```bash
python build_and_run.py
```

This will:

1. Compile `main.cpp` using `emcc`
2. Output to the `build/` folder
3. Start a local dev server at [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)

---

